-- Egyptian Stocks: Orascom Telecom Holding, Oriental Weavers
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-05-06T13:10:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/egyptian-stocks-orascom-telecom-holding-oriental-weavers.html
Egypt’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30)  rose 0.9
percent to 4,973.62 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo, the highest
level in more than a month.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)   retreated as much as
2.7 percent to 3.22 Egyptian pounds before closing at 3.29
pounds. Shareholders of North Africa’s biggest mobile-phone
company approved borrowing $2.5 billion from  VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP)  at
an interest rate of 12.5 percent for as long as five years.  Oriental Weavers Co. (ORWE)   increased 1.9 percent, the
most in a week, to 19.22 pounds, the highest level in two weeks.
Egypt’s biggest carpets manufacturer will pay a 1.50-pound
dividend per share on May 17.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
